<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<hr>
 <ol>
<li>
<a href="#head-5a7ec9ed375f5891a77ecc3ede00f1778c31f2d2">The Quest</a></li>
<li>
<a href="#head-31904f2dc3fa4d447ef2ead25fb8fcc4ae3ef2b0">Class-specific tactics</a></li>
</ol>

 <hr>
 <h3 id="head-5a7ec9ed375f5891a77ecc3ede00f1778c31f2d2"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>The Quest</h3>
Goal: Your goal is simply to reach the exit staircase, which lies in the southeast corner of a fairly small quest level. You do not <em>have</em> to kill anything. <p>
Monsters: Buckets and buckets of trolls, arrayed in a diagonal grid. There are spaces in-between each troll. The worst of the lot are a number of Hrus which are toward the center of the level. Ulik the Troll is also found on this level, and some Ancient Green Dragons. You may think more trolls are being summoned, but they are not; there's simply a lot of them there. 
</p>
<p>
Tactics:  
</p>

    <ol type="1">

    <li>
<p>
Stealth: Characters with very high stealth can simply tiptoe through without waking up anything.  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
Mayhem: Serious mayhem is required to get through this quest on brute force.  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
Magic: Many people speak well of Wands of Tidal Wave for this quest. Junkarts of Genocide are helpful to eradicate the Hrus. 
</p>
</li>

    </ol>


<p>
The reward for your success: You get access to the Expensive Jewelry Store in Gondolin, which appears to the left of the entrance to the Mayor's office.You also obtain 200000 gold pieces if at least 2/3 of the monsters are killed. 
</p>
<h3 id="head-31904f2dc3fa4d447ef2ead25fb8fcc4ae3ef2b0"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Class-specific tactics</h3>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Missile-using characters: Use exploding ammos of Gravity to blast a clear pathway through. I just did this quest with an Archer. I was missing a Genocide junkart to cope with the Hrus. I *wanted* to try to kill all the monsters, but it just didn't work out that way, and the exploding Gravity arrows I happened to have got me through it very, very easily. 
</p>
</li>
</ul>

